ASC.name: ASC
ASC.description: For double-byte character set (DBCS) languages, the function changes full-width (double-byte) characters to half-width (single-byte) characters.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The text or a reference to a cell containing the text to change.

CHAR.name: CHAR
CHAR.description: Returns the character specified by the code number from your computer's character set.

params.name: arg1
params.description: A number between 1 and 255 specifying a character from the computer character set.

CLEAN.name: CLEAN
CLEAN.description: Removes all the nonprintable characters from the text.

params.name: arg1
params.description: A string from which nonprintable characters will be removed.

CODE.name: CODE
CODE.description: Returns the code number from your computer's character set for the first character in the specified text string.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The text for which to get the code of the first character.

CONCATENATE.name: CONCATENATE
CONCATENATE.description: Combines multiple text strings into one text string.

params.name: arg_n
params.description: Up to 255 data values that will be combined.

DOLLAR.name: DOLLAR
DOLLAR.description: Converts a number to text, using a currency format $#.##.

params.name: arg1
params.description: A number, a reference to a cell containing a number, or a formula that returns a number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: A number of digits to the right of the decimal point. The number is rounded as necessary. If it is omitted, the function will assume it to be 2.

EXACT.name: EXACT
EXACT.description: Checks whether two text strings are exactly the same, and returns true or false. This function is case-sensitive.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The first text string.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The second text string.

FIND.name: FIND
FIND.description: Returns the starting position of one text string within another text string. This function is case-sensitive.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The text to find. Use double quotes (empty text) to match the first character in the search string. Wildcard characters are not allowed.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The text containing the text to find.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Specifies the character at which to start the search. The first character in the search string is character number 1. If omitted, this parameter is equal to 1.

FINDB.name: FINDB
FINDB.description: Finds the specified substring within another string and is intended for languages that use the double-byte character set (DBCS) like Japanese, Chinese, Korean etc.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The text to find. Use double quotes (empty text) to match the first character in the search string. Wildcard characters are not allowed.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The text containing the text to find.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Specifies the character at which to start the search. The first character in the search string is character number 1. If omitted, this parameter is equal to 1.

FIXED.name: FIXED
FIXED.description: Rounds a number to the specified number of decimals and returns the result as text with or without commas.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The number to round and convert to text.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The number of digits to the right of the decimal point. If omitted, the function will assume it to be 2.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Specifies whether do display commas in the returned text (false or omitted) or not (true).

LEFT.name: LEFT
LEFT.description: Returns the specified number of characters from the start of a text string.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The text string containing the characters to extract.

params.name: arg2
params.description: A number of the substring characters. It must be greater than or equal to 0.

LEFTB.name: LEFTB
LEFTB.description: Extracts the substring from the specified string starting from the left character and is intended for languages that use the double-byte character set (DBCS) like Japanese, Chinese, Korean etc.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The text string containing the characters to extract.

params.name: arg2
params.description: A number of the substring characters, based on bytes.

LEN.name: LEN
LEN.description: Returns the number of characters in a text string.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The text whose length will be returned. Spaces are considered as characters.

LENB.name: LENB
LENB.description: Analyses the specified string and returns the number of characters it contains and is intended for languages that use the double-byte character set (DBCS) like Japanese, Chinese, Korean etc.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The text whose length will be returned. Spaces are considered as characters.

LOWER.name: LOWER
LOWER.description: Converts all letters in a text string to lowercase.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The text to convert to lowercase. The text characters that are not letters are not changed.

MID.name: MID
MID.description: Returns the characters from the middle of a text string, given a starting position and length.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The text string from which to extract the characters.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The position of the first character to extract. The first text character is 1.

params.name: arg3
params.description: A number of the characters to extract.

MIDB.name: MIDB
MIDB.description: Extracts the characters from the specified string starting from any position and is intended for languages that use the double-byte character set (DBCS) like Japanese, Chinese, Korean etc.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The text string from which to extract the characters.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The position of the first character to extract. The first text character is 1.

params.name: arg3
params.description: A number of the characters to extract, based on bytes.

NUMBERVALUE.name: NUMBERVALUE
NUMBERVALUE.description: Converts text to a number, in a locale-independent way.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The string representing a number to convert.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The character used as the decimal separator in the string.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The character used as the group separator in the string.

PROPER.name: PROPER
PROPER.description: Converts a text string to proper case: the first letter in each word to uppercase, and all other letters to lowercase.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The text enclosed in quotation marks, a formula that returns text, or a reference to a cell containing text to partially capitalize.

REPLACE.name: REPLACE
REPLACE.description: Replaces part of a text string with a different text string.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The text where some characters will be replaced.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The position of the character in the original text that will be replaced with the new text.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The number of characters in the original text that will be replaced.

params.name: arg4
params.description: The text that will replace characters in the original text.

REPLACEB.name: REPLACEB
REPLACEB.description: Replaces a set of characters, based on the number of characters and the start position specified, with a new set of characters and is intended for languages that use the double-byte character set (DBCS) like Japanese, Chinese, Korean etc.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The text where some characters will be replaced.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The position of the character in the original text that will be replaced with the new text.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The number of characters in the original text that will be replaced, based on bytes.

params.name: arg4
params.description: The text that will replace characters in the original text.

REPT.name: REPT
REPT.description: Repeats text a given number of times. Use this function to fill a cell with a number of instances of a text string.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The text that will be repeated.

params.name: arg2
params.description: A positive number specifying the number of times to repeat text.

RIGHT.name: RIGHT
RIGHT.description: Returns the specified number of characters from the end of a text string.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The text string that contains the characters to extract.

params.name: arg2
params.description: A number of the substring characters. If it is omitted, the function will assume it to be 1.

RIGHTB.name: RIGHTB
RIGHTB.description: Extracts a substring from a string starting from the right-most character, based on the specified number of characters and is intended for languages that use the double-byte character set (DBCS) like Japanese, Chinese, Korean etc.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The text string that contains the characters to extract.

params.name: arg2
params.description: A number of the substring characters, based on bytes.

SEARCH.name: SEARCH
SEARCH.description: Returns the number of the character at which a specific character or text string is first found, reading left to right (not case-sensitive).

params.name: arg1
params.description: The text to find. The ? and * wildcard characters can be used. Use ~? and ~* to find the ? and * characters.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The text where to search for the specified text.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The character number in the search text, counting from the left, at which to start searching. If omitted, 1 is used.

SEARCHB.name: SEARCHB
SEARCHB.description: Returns the location of the specified substring in a string and is intended for languages that use the double-byte character set (DBCS) like Japanese, Chinese, Korean etc.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The text to find. The ? and * wildcard characters can be used. Use ~? and ~* to find the ? and * characters.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The text where to search for the specified text.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The character number in the search text, counting from the left, at which to start searching. If omitted, 1 is used.

SUBSTITUTE.name: SUBSTITUTE
SUBSTITUTE.description: Replaces existing text with new text in a text string.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The text or the reference to a cell containing text in which the characters will be substituted.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The existing text to replace. If the case of the original text does not match the case of text, the function will not replace the text.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The text to replace the original text with.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Specifies which occurrence of the original text to replace. If omitted, every instance of the original text will be replaced.

T.name: T
T.description: Checks whether a value is text, and returns the text if it is, or returns double quotes (empty text) if it is not.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The value to test.

TEXT.name: TEXT
TEXT.description: Converts a value to text in a specific number format.

params.name: arg1
params.description: A number, a formula that evaluates to a numeric value, or a reference to a cell containing a numeric value.

params.name: arg2
params.description: A number format in the text form from the Number format combo box on the Home tab.

TRIM.name: TRIM
TRIM.description: Removes all spaces from a text string except for single spaces between words.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The text from which the spaces will be removed.

UNICHAR.name: UNICHAR
UNICHAR.description: Returns the Unicode character referenced by the given numeric value.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The Unicode number representing a character.

UNICODE.name: UNICODE
UNICODE.description: Returns the number (code point) corresponding to the first character of the text.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The character for which the Unicode value will be returned.

UPPER.name: UPPER
UPPER.description: Converts a text string to all uppercase letters.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The text which will be converted to uppercase, a reference or a text string.

VALUE.name: VALUE
VALUE.description: Converts a text string that represents a number to a number.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The text enclosed in quotation marks or a reference to a cell containing the text which will be converted to a number.

AVEDEV.name: AVEDEV
AVEDEV.description: Returns the average of the absolute deviations of data points from their mean.

params.name: args
params.description: Up to 255 numeric values for which the average of the absolute deviations will be returned. The first argument is required, subsequent arguments are optional. Arguments can be numbers or names, arrays or references that contain numbers.

AVERAGE.name: AVERAGE
AVERAGE.description: Returns the average (arithmetic mean) of the specified arguments.

params.name: args
params.description: Up to 255 numeric values for which the average value will be returned. The first argument is required, subsequent arguments are optional. Arguments can be numbers or names, arrays or references that contain numbers.

AVERAGEA.name: AVERAGEA
AVERAGEA.description: Returns the average (arithmetic mean) of the specified arguments, evaluating text and false in arguments as 0; true evaluates as 1.

params.name: args
params.description: Up to 255 numeric values for which the average value will be returned. The first argument is required, subsequent arguments are optional. Arguments can be numbers or names, arrays or references that contain numbers, text representations of numbers, or logical values, such as true and false.

AVERAGEIF.name: AVERAGEIF
AVERAGEIF.description: Finds the average (arithmetic mean) for the cells specified by a given condition or criteria.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The range of cells which will be evaluated.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The condition or criteria in the form of a number, expression, or text that defines which cells will be used to find the average.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The actual cells to be used to find the average. If omitted, the cells in the range are used.

AVERAGEIFS.name: AVERAGEIFS
AVERAGEIFS.description: Finds the average (arithmetic mean) for the cells specified by a given set of conditions or criteria.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The range of cells which will be evaluated.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The first condition or criteria in the form of a number, expression, or text that defines which cells will be used to find the average.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The actual cells to be used to find the average. If omitted, the cells in the range are used.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Up to 127 additional conditions or criteria in the form of a number, expression, or text that defines which cells will be used to find the average. These arguments are optional.

params.name: arg5
params.description: Up to 127 actual ranges to be used to find the average. If omitted, the cells in the range are used. These arguments are optional.

BETADIST.name: BETADIST
BETADIST.description: Returns the cumulative beta probability density function.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The value between A and B at which to evaluate the function.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The alpha parameter of the distribution which must be greater than 0.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The beta parameter of the distribution which must be greater than 0.

params.name: arg4
params.description: An optional lower bound to the interval of x (A). If omitted, it is equal to 0.

params.name: arg5
params.description: An optional upper bound to the interval of x (B). If omitted, it is equal to 1.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The value between A and B at which to evaluate the function.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The alpha parameter of the distribution which must be greater than 0.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The beta parameter of the distribution which must be greater than 0.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Specifies if this is the cumulative distribution function (true) or the probability density function (false).

params.name: arg5
params.description: An optional lower bound to the interval of x (A). If omitted, it is equal to 0.

params.name: arg6
params.description: An optional upper bound to the interval of x (B). If omitted, it is equal to 1.

BETA_INV.name: BETA_INV
BETA_INV.description: Returns the inverse of the cumulative beta probability density function (BETA_DIST).

params.name: arg1
params.description: A probability associated with the beta distribution.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The alpha parameter of the distribution which must be greater than 0.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The beta parameter of the distribution which must be greater than 0.

params.name: arg4
params.description: An optional lower bound to the interval of x (A). If omitted, it is equal to 0.

params.name: arg5
params.description: An optional upper bound to the interval of x (B). If omitted, it is equal to 1.

BETAINV.name: BETAINV
BETAINV.description: Returns the inverse of the cumulative beta probability density function for a specified beta distribution (BETADIST).

params.name: arg1
params.description: A probability associated with the beta distribution.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The alpha parameter of the distribution which must be greater than 0.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The beta parameter of the distribution which must be greater than 0.

params.name: arg4
params.description: An optional lower bound to the interval of x (A). If omitted, it is equal to 0.

params.name: arg5
params.description: An optional upper bound to the interval of x (B). If omitted, it is equal to 1.

BINOMDIST.name: BINOMDIST
BINOMDIST.description: Returns the individual term binomial distribution probability.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The number of successes in trials.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The number of independent trials.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The probability of success on each trial.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Specifies if this is the cumulative distribution function (true) or the probability mass function (false).

BINOM_DIST.name: BINOM_DIST
BINOM_DIST.description: Returns the individual term binomial distribution probability.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The number of successes in trials.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The number of independent trials.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The probability of success on each trial.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Specifies if this is the cumulative distribution function (true) or the probability mass function (false).

BINOM_DIST_RANGE.name: BINOM_DIST_RANGE
BINOM_DIST_RANGE.description: Returns the probability of a trial result using a binomial distribution.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The number of independent trials.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The probability of success on each trial.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The minimum number of successes in the trials to calculate probability for, a numeric value greater than or equal to 0.

params.name: arg4
params.description: The maximum number of successes in the trials to calculate probability for, a numeric value greater than the minimum number of successes and less than or equal to trials.

BINOM_INV.name: BINOM_INV
BINOM_INV.description: Returns the smallest value for which the cumulative binomial distribution is greater than or equal to a criterion value.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The number of Bernoulli trials.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The probability of success on each trial, a number between 0 and 1 inclusive.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The criterion value, a number between 0 and 1 inclusive.

CHIDIST.name: CHIDIST
CHIDIST.description: Returns the right-tailed probability of the chi-squared distribution.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The value at which the distribution will be evaluated, a nonnegative number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The number of degrees of freedom, a number between 1 and 10^10, excluding 10^10.

CHIINV.name: CHIINV
CHIINV.description: Returns the inverse of the right-tailed probability of the chi-squared distribution.

params.name: arg1
params.description: A probability associated with the chi-squared distribution, a value between 0 and 1 inclusive.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The number of degrees of freedom, a number between 1 and 10^10, excluding 10^10.

CHISQ_DIST.name: CHISQ_DIST
CHISQ_DIST.description: Returns the left-tailed probability of the chi-squared distribution.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The value at which the distribution will be evaluated, a nonnegative number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The number of degrees of freedom, a number between 1 and 10^10, excluding 10^10.

params.name: arg3
params.description: A logical value that determines the form of the function. If this argument is equal to true, the cumulative distribution function is returned; if it is equal to false, the probability density function is returned.

CHISQ_DIST_RT.name: CHISQ_DIST_RT
CHISQ_DIST_RT.description: Returns the right-tailed probability of the chi-squared distribution.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The value at which the distribution will be evaluated, a nonnegative number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The number of degrees of freedom, a number between 1 and 10^10, excluding 10^10.

CHISQ_INV.name: CHISQ_INV
CHISQ_INV.description: Returns the inverse of the left-tailed probability of the chi-squared distribution.

params.name: arg1
params.description: A probability associated with the chi-squared distribution, a value between 0 and 1 inclusive.

params.name: arg2-
params.description: The number of degrees of freedom, a number between 1 and 10^10, excluding 10^10.

CHISQ_INV_RT.name: CHISQ_INV_RT
CHISQ_INV_RT.description: Returns the inverse of the right-tailed probability of the chi-squared distribution.

params.name: arg1
params.description: A probability associated with the chi-squared distribution, a value between 0 and 1 inclusive.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The number of degrees of freedom, a number between 1 and 10^10, excluding 10^10.

CHITEST.name: CHITEST
CHITEST.description: Returns the test for independence: the value from the chi-squared distribution for the statistic and the appropriate degrees of freedom.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The range of data that contains observations to test against expected values.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The range of data that contains the ratio of the product of row totals and column totals to the grand total.

CONFIDENCE.name: CONFIDENCE
CONFIDENCE.description: Returns the confidence interval for a population mean, using a normal distribution.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The significance level used to compute the confidence level, a number greater than 0 and less than 1.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The population standard deviation for the data range and is assumed to be known. This value must be greater than 0.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The sample size.

CONFIDENCE_NORM.name: CONFIDENCE_NORM
CONFIDENCE_NORM.description: Returns the confidence interval for a population mean, using a normal distribution.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The significance level used to compute the confidence level, a number greater than 0 and less than 1.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The population standard deviation for the data range and is assumed to be known. This value must be greater than 0.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The sample size.

CONFIDENCE_T.name: CONFIDENCE_T
CONFIDENCE_T.description: Returns the confidence interval for a population mean, using a Student's t distribution.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The significance level used to compute the confidence level, a number greater than 0 and less than 1.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The population standard deviation for the data range and is assumed to be known. This value must be greater than 0.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The sample size.

COUNT.name: COUNT
COUNT.description: Counts a number of cells in a range that contains numbers ignoring empty cells or those contaning text.

params.name: args
params.description: Up to 255 items, cell references, or ranges to count numbers. The first argument is required, subsequent arguments are optional.

COUNTA.name: COUNTA
COUNTA.description: Counts a number of cells in a range that are not empty.

params.name: args
params.description: Up to 255 items, cell references, or ranges to count values. The first argument is required, subsequent arguments are optional.

COUNTBLANK.name: COUNTBLANK
COUNTBLANK.description: Counts a number of empty cells in a specified range of cells.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The range to count the empty cells.

COUNTIF.name: COUNTIF
COUNTIF.description: Counts a number of cells within a range that meet the given condition.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The range of cells to count nonblank cells.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The condition in the form of a number, expression, or text that defines which cells will be counted.

COUNTIFS.name: COUNTIFS
COUNTIFS.description: Counts a number of cells specified by a given set of conditions or criteria.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The first range of cells to count nonblank cells.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The first condition in the form of a number, expression, or text that defines which cells will be counted.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Up to 127 additional ranges of cells to count nonblank cells. This argument is optional.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Up to 127 additional conditions in the form of a number, expression, or text that define which cells will be counted.

CRITBINOM.name: CRITBINOM
CRITBINOM.description: Returns the smallest value for which the cumulative binomial distribution is greater than or equal to a criterion value.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The number of Bernoulli trials.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The probability of success on each trial, a number between 0 and 1 inclusive.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The criterion value, a number between 0 and 1 inclusive.

DEVSQ.name: DEVSQ
DEVSQ.description: Returns the sum of squares of deviations of data points from their sample mean.

params.name: args
params.description: Up to 255 numerical values for which to find the sum of squares of deviations. The first argument is required, subsequent arguments are optional.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The value of the x function, a nonnegative number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The lambda parameter value, a positive number.

params.name: arg3
params.description: A logical value that determines the function form. If this parameter is true, the function will return the cumulative distribution function, if it is false, it will return the probability density function.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The value of the x function, a nonnegative number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The lambda parameter value, a positive number.

params.name: arg3
params.description: A logical value that determines the function form. If this parameter is true, the function will return the cumulative distribution function, if it is false, it will return the probability density function.

F_DIST.name: F_DIST
F_DIST.description: Returns the (left-tailed) F probability distribution (degree of diversity) for two data sets.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The value at which to evaluate the function, a nonnegative number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The numerator degrees of freedom, a number between 1 and 10^10, excluding 10^10.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The denominator degrees of freedom, a number between 1 and 10^10, excluding 10^10.

params.name: arg4
params.description: A logical value that determines the function form. If this parameter is true, the function will return the cumulative distribution function, if it is false, it will return the probability density function.

FDIST.name: FDIST
FDIST.description: Returns the (right-tailed) F probability distribution (degree of diversity) for two data sets.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The value at which to evaluate the function, a nonnegative number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The numerator degrees of freedom, a number between 1 and 10^10, excluding 10^10.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The denominator degrees of freedom, a number between 1 and 10^10, excluding 10^10.

F_DIST_RT.name: F_DIST_RT
F_DIST_RT.description: Returns the (right-tailed) F probability distribution (degree of diversity) for two data sets.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The value at which to evaluate the function, a nonnegative number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The numerator degrees of freedom, a number between 1 and 10^10, excluding 10^10.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The denominator degrees of freedom, a number between 1 and 10^10, excluding 10^10.

F_INV.name: F_INV
F_INV.description: Returns the inverse of the (left-tailed) F probability distribution: if p = F.DIST(x,...), then F.INV(p,...) = x.

params.name: arg1
params.description: A probability associated with the F cumulative distribution, a number between 0 and 1 inclusive.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The numerator degrees of freedom, a number between 1 and 10^10, excluding 10^10.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The denominator degrees of freedom, a number between 1 and 10^10, excluding 10^10.

FINV.name: FINV
FINV.description: Returns the inverse of the (right-tailed) F probability distribution: if p = FDIST(x,...), then FINV(p,...) = x.

params.name: arg1
params.description: A probability associated with the F cumulative distribution, a number between 0 and 1 inclusive.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The numerator degrees of freedom, a number between 1 and 10^10, excluding 10^10.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The denominator degrees of freedom, a number between 1 and 10^10, excluding 10^10.

F_INV_RT.name: F_INV_RT
F_INV_RT.description: Returns the inverse of the (right-tailed) F probability distribution: if p = F.DIST.RT(x,...), then F.INV.RT(p,...) = x.

params.name: arg1
params.description: A probability associated with the F cumulative distribution, a number between 0 and 1 inclusive.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The numerator degrees of freedom, a number between 1 and 10^10, excluding 10^10.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The denominator degrees of freedom, a number between 1 and 10^10, excluding 10^10.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The value for the transformation, a number between -1 and 1, excluding -1 and 1.

FISHERINV.name: FISHERINV
FISHERINV.description: Returns the inverse of the Fisher transformation: if y = FISHER(x), then FISHERINV(y) = x.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The value to perform the inverse of the transformation.

FORECAST_ETS.name: FORECAST_ETS
FORECAST_ETS.description: Сalculates or predicts a future value based on existing (historical) values by using the AAA version of the Exponential Smoothing (ETS) algorithm.

params.name: arg1
params.description: A date for which a new value will be predicted. Must be after the last date in the timeline.

params.name: arg2
params.description: A range or an array of numeric data that determines the historical values for which a new point will be predicted.

params.name: arg3
params.description: A range of date/time values that correspond to the historical values. The timeline range must be of the same size as the second argument. Date/time values must have a constant step between them and can't be zero.

params.name: arg4
params.description: An optional numeric value that specifies the length of the seasonal pattern. The default value of 1 indicates seasonality is detected automatically. The 0 value means no seasonality.

params.name: arg5
params.description: An optional numeric value to handle missing values. The default value of 1 replaces missing values by interpolation, and 0 replaces them with zeros.

params.name: arg6
params.description: An optional numeric value to aggregate multiple values with the same time stamp.

FORECAST_ETS_CONFINT.name: FORECAST_ETS_CONFINT
FORECAST_ETS_CONFINT.description: Returns a confidence interval for the forecast value at the specified target date.

params.name: arg1
params.description: A date for which a new value will be predicted. Must be after the last date in the timeline.

params.name: arg2
params.description: A range or an array of numeric data that determines the historical values for which a new point will be predicted.

params.name: arg3
params.description: A range of date/time values that correspond to the historical values. The timeline range must be of the same size as the second argument. Date/time values must have a constant step between them and can't be zero.

params.name: arg4
params.description: A number between 0 and 1 that shows the confidence level for the calculated confidence interval. The default value is .95.

params.name: arg5
params.description: An optional numeric value that specifies the length of the seasonal pattern. The default value of 1 indicates seasonality is detected automatically. The 0 value means no seasonality.

params.name: arg6
params.description: An optional numeric value to handle missing values. The default value of 1 replaces missing values by interpolation, and 0 replaces them with zeros.

params.name: arg7
params.description: An optional numeric value to aggregate multiple values with the same time stamp.

FORECAST_ETS_SEASONALITY.name: FORECAST_ETS_SEASONALITY
FORECAST_ETS_SEASONALITY.description: Returns the length of the repetitive pattern an application detects for the specified time series.

params.name: arg1
params.description: A range or an array of numeric data that determines the historical values for which a new point will be predicted.

params.name: arg2
params.description: A range of date/time values that correspond to the historical values. The timeline range must be of the same size as the second argument. Date/time values must have a constant step between them and can't be zero.

params.name: arg3
params.description: An optional numeric value to handle missing values. The default value of 1 replaces missing values by interpolation, and 0 replaces them with zeros.

params.name: arg4
params.description: An optional numeric value to aggregate multiple values with the same time stamp.

FORECAST_ETS_STAT.name: FORECAST_ETS_STAT
FORECAST_ETS_STAT.description: Returns the requested statistic for the forecast.

params.name: arg1
params.description: A range or an array of numeric data that determines the historical values for which a new point will be predicted.

params.name: arg2
params.description: A range of date/time values that correspond to the historical values. The timeline range must be of the same size as the second argument. Date/time values must have a constant step between them and can't be zero.

params.name: arg3
params.description: A number between 1 and 8, indicating which statistic will be returned for the calculated forecast.

params.name: arg4
params.description: An optional numeric value that specifies the length of the seasonal pattern. The default value of 1 indicates seasonality is detected automatically. The 0 value means no seasonality.

params.name: arg5
params.description: An optional numeric value to handle missing values. The default value of 1 replaces missing values by interpolation, and 0 replaces them with zeros.

params.name: arg6
params.description: An optional numeric value to aggregate multiple values with the same time stamp.

FREQUENCY.name: FREQUENCY
FREQUENCY.description: Calculates how often values occur within a range of values and then returns the first value of the returned vertical array of numbers.

params.name: arg1
params.description: An array of values or the selected range for which the frequencies will be counted (blanks and text are ignored).

params.name: arg2
params.description: An array of intervals or the selected range into which the values in the first array will be grouped.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The value for which the gamma function will be calculated.

params.name: arg2

params.name: arg3

params.name: arg4

GAMMA_INV.name: GAMMA_INV
GAMMA_INV.description: Returns the inverse of the gamma cumulative distribution: if p = GAMMA.DIST(x,...), then GAMMA.INV(p,...) = x.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The probability associated with the gamma distribution, a number between 0 and 1, inclusive.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The alpha parameter of the distribution, a positive number.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The beta parameter of the distribution, a positive number. If this parameter is equal to 1, the function returns the standard gamma distribution.

GAMMAINV.name: GAMMAINV
GAMMAINV.description: Returns the inverse of the gamma cumulative distribution: if p = GAMMADIST(x,...), then GAMMAINV(p,...) = x.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The probability associated with the gamma distribution, a number between 0 and 1, inclusive.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The alpha parameter of the distribution, a positive number.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The beta parameter of the distribution, a positive number. If this parameter is equal to 1, the function returns the standard gamma distribution.

GAMMALN.name: GAMMALN
GAMMALN.description: Returns the natural logarithm of the gamma function.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The value for which the natural logarithm of the gamma function will be calculated, a positive number.

GAMMALN_PRECISE.name: GAMMALN_PRECISE
GAMMALN_PRECISE.description: Returns the natural logarithm of the gamma function.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The value for which the natural logarithm of the gamma function will be calculated, a positive number.

GAUSS.name: GAUSS
GAUSS.description: Calculates the probability that a member of a standard normal population will fall between the mean and arg1 standard deviations from the mean.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The value for which the distribution will be calculated.

GEOMEAN.name: GEOMEAN
GEOMEAN.description: Returns the geometric mean of an array or range of positive numeric data.

params.name: args
params.description: Up to 255 numeric values for which the geometric mean will be calculated.

GROWTH.name: GROWTH
GROWTH.description: Calculates predicted exponential growth by using existing data.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The set of y-values from the y = b*m^x equation, an array or range of positive numbers.

params.name: arg2
params.description: An optional set of x-values from the y = b*m^x equation, an array or range of positive numbers that has the same size as the set of y-values.

params.name: arg3
params.description: New x-values for which the function will return the corresponding y-values.

params.name: arg4
params.description: A logical value: the constant b is calculated normally if this parameter is set to true, and b is set equal to 1 if the parameter is false or omitted.

HARMEAN.name: HARMEAN
HARMEAN.description: Returns the harmonic mean of a data set of positive numbers: the reciprocal of the arithmetic mean of reciprocals.

params.name: args
params.description: Up to 255 numeric values for which the harmonic mean will be calculated.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The number of successes in the sample.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The size of the sample.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The number of successes in the population.

params.name: arg4
params.description: The population size.

params.description: The number of successes in the sample.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The size of the sample.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The number of successes in the population.

params.name: arg4
params.description: The population size.

params.name: arg5
params.description: A logical value (true or false) that determines the function form. If it is true, the function returns the cumulative distribution function. If it is false, the function returns the probability mass function.

KURT.name: KURT
KURT.description: Returns the kurtosis of a data set.

params.name: args
params.description: Up to 255 numeric values for which the kurtosis will be calculated.

LARGE.name: LARGE
LARGE.description: Returns the k-th largest value in a data set. For example, the fifth largest number.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The array or range of data for which the k-th largest value will be determined.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The position (from the largest) in the array or cell range of data to return.

LINEST.name: LINEST
LINEST.description: Returns statistics that describe a linear trend matching known data points, by fitting a straight line using the least squares method.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The set of y-values from the y = mx + b equation.

params.name: arg2
params.description: An optional set of x-values from the y = mx + b equation.

params.name: arg3
params.description: A logical value: the constant b is calculated normally if this parameter is set to true or omitted, and b is set equal to 0 if the parameter is false.

params.name: arg4
params.description: A logical value: return additional regression statistics if this parameter is set to true, and return m-coefficients and the constant b if the parameter is false or omitted.

LOGEST.name: LOGEST
LOGEST.description: Returns statistics that describe an exponential curve matching known data points.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The set of y-values from the y = b*m^x equation.

params.name: arg2
params.description: An optional set of x-values from the y = b*m^x equation.

params.name: arg3
params.description: A logical value: the constant b is calculated normally if this parameter is set to true or omitted, and b is set equal to 1 if the parameter is false.

params.name: arg4
params.description: A logical value: return additional regression statistics if this parameter is set to true, and return m-coefficients and the constant b if the parameter is false or omitted.

LOGINV.name: LOGINV
LOGINV.description: Returns the inverse of the lognormal cumulative distribution function of x, where ln(x) is normally distributed with the specified parameters.

params.name: arg1
params.description: A probability associated with the lognormal distribution, a number between 0 and 1, inclusive.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The mean of ln(x).

params.name: arg3
params.description: The standard deviation of ln(x), a positive number.

LOGNORM_DIST.name: LOGNORM_DIST
LOGNORM_DIST.description: Returns the lognormal distribution of x, where ln(x) is normally distributed with the specified parameters.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The value at which to evaluate the function, a positive number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The mean of ln(x).

params.name: arg3
params.description: The standard deviation of ln(x), a positive number.

params.name: arg4
params.description: A logical value (true or false) that determines the function form. If it is true, the function returns the cumulative distribution function. If it is false, the function returns the probability density function.

LOGNORM_INV.name: LOGNORM_INV
LOGNORM_INV.description: Returns the inverse of the lognormal cumulative distribution function of x, where ln(x) is normally distributed with the specified parameters.

params.name: arg1
params.description: A probability associated with the lognormal distribution, a number between 0 and 1, inclusive.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The mean of ln(x).

params.name: arg3
params.description: The standard deviation of ln(x), a positive number.

LOGNORMDIST.name: LOGNORMDIST
LOGNORMDIST.description: Returns the cumulative lognormal distribution of x, where ln(x) is normally distributed with the specified parameters.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The value at which to evaluate the function, a positive number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The mean of ln(x).

params.name: arg3
params.description: The standard deviation of ln(x), a positive number.

MAX.name: MAX
MAX.description: Returns the largest value in a set of values. Ignores logical values and text.

params.name: args
params.description: Up to 255 numeric values for which the largest number will be returned. The first argument is required, subsequent arguments are optional.

MAXA.name: MAXA
MAXA.description: Returns the largest value in a set of values. Does not ignore logical values and text.

params.name: args
params.description: Up to 255 values (number, text, logical value) for which the largest value will be returned. The first argument is required, subsequent arguments are optional.

MEDIAN.name: MEDIAN
MEDIAN.description: Returns the median, or the number in the middle of the set of given numbers.

params.name: args
params.description: Up to 255 numeric values for which the median will be calculated. The first argument is required, subsequent arguments are optional.

MIN.name: MIN
MIN.description: Returns the smallest number in a set of values. Ignores logical values and text.

params.name: args
params.description: Up to 255 numeric values for which the smallest number will be returned. The first argument is required, subsequent arguments are optional.

MINA.name: MINA
MINA.description: Returns the smallest value in a set of values. Does not ignore logical values and text.

params.name: args
params.description: Up to 255 values (number, text, logical value) for which the smallest value will be returned. The first argument is required, subsequent arguments are optional.

NEGBINOMDIST.name: NEGBINOMDIST
NEGBINOMDIST.description: Returns the negative binomial distribution, the probability that there will be the specified number of failures before the last success, with the specified probability of a success.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The number of failures.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The threshold number of successes.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The probability of a success; a number between 0 and 1.

NEGBINOM_DIST.name: NEGBINOM_DIST
NEGBINOM_DIST.description: Returns the negative binomial distribution, the probability that there will be the specified number of failures before the last success, with the specified probability of a success.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The number of failures.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The threshold number of successes.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The probability of a success; a number between 0 and 1.

params.name: arg4
params.description: A logical value (true or false) that determines the function form. If it is true, the function returns the cumulative distribution function. If it is false, the function returns the probability density function.

NORMDIST.name: NORMDIST
NORMDIST.description: Returns the normal cumulative distribution for the specified mean and standard deviation.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The value for which the distribution will be returned.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The arithmetic mean of the distribution.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The standard deviation of the distribution, a positive number.

params.name: arg4
params.description: A logical value (true or false) that determines the function form. If it is true, the function returns the cumulative distribution function. If it is false, the function returns the probability mass function.

NORM_DIST.name: NORM_DIST
NORM_DIST.description: Returns the normal distribution for the specified mean and standard deviation.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The value for which the distribution will be returned.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The arithmetic mean of the distribution.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The standard deviation of the distribution, a positive number.

params.name: arg4
params.description: A logical value (true or false) that determines the function form. If it is true, the function returns the cumulative distribution function. If it is false, the function returns the probability mass function.

NORMINV.name: NORMINV
NORMINV.description: Returns the inverse of the normal cumulative distribution for the specified mean and standard deviation.

params.name: arg1
params.description: A probability corresponding to the normal distribution, a number between 0 and 1 inclusive.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The arithmetic mean of the distribution.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The standard deviation of the distribution, a positive number.

NORM_INV.name: NORM_INV
NORM_INV.description: Returns the inverse of the normal cumulative distribution for the specified mean and standard deviation.

params.name: arg1
params.description: A probability corresponding to the normal distribution, a number between 0 and 1 inclusive.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The arithmetic mean of the distribution.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The standard deviation of the distribution, a positive number.

NORMSDIST.name: NORMSDIST
NORMSDIST.description: Returns the standard normal cumulative distribution (has a mean of zero and a standard deviation of one).

params.name: arg1
params.description: The value for which the distribution will be returned.

NORM_S_DIST.name: NORM_S_DIST
NORM_S_DIST.description: Returns the standard normal distribution (has a mean of zero and a standard deviation of one).

params.name: arg1
params.description: The value for which the distribution will be returned.

params.name: arg2
params.description: A logical value (true or false) that determines the function form. If it is true, the function returns the cumulative distribution function. If it is false, the function returns the probability mass function.

NORMSINV.name: NORMSINV
NORMSINV.description: Returns the inverse of the standard normal cumulative distribution (has a mean of zero and a standard deviation of one).

params.name: arg1
params.description: A probability corresponding to the normal distribution, a number between 0 and 1 inclusive.

NORM_S_INV.name: NORM_S_INV
NORM_S_INV.description: Returns the inverse of the standard normal cumulative distribution (has a mean of zero and a standard deviation of one).

params.name: arg1
params.description: A probability corresponding to the normal distribution, a number between 0 and 1 inclusive.

PERCENTILE.name: PERCENTILE
PERCENTILE.description: Returns the k-th percentile of values in a range.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The array or range of data that defines relative standing.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The percentile value that is equal to 0 but less than or equal to 1.

PERCENTILE_EXC.name: PERCENTILE_EXC
PERCENTILE_EXC.description: Returns the k-th percentile of values in a range, where k is in the range 0..1, exclusive.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The array or range of data that defines relative standing.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The percentile value that is greater than 0 but less than 1.

PERCENTILE_INC.name: PERCENTILE_INC
PERCENTILE_INC.description: Returns the k-th percentile of values in a range, where k is in the range 0..1, inclusive.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The array or range of data that defines relative standing.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The percentile value that is equal to 0 but less than or equal to 1.

PERCENTRANK.name: PERCENTRANK
PERCENTRANK.description: Returns the rank of a value in a data set as a percentage of the data set.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The array or range of data with numeric values that defines relative standing.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The value for which the rank will be returned.

params.name: arg3
params.description: An optional value that identifies the number of significant digits for the returned percentage, three digits if omitted (0.xxx%).

PERCENTRANK_EXC.name: PERCENTRANK_EXC
PERCENTRANK_EXC.description: Returns the rank of a value in a data set as a percentage (0..1, exclusive) of the data set.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The array or range of data with numeric values that defines relative standing.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The value for which the rank will be returned.

params.name: arg3
params.description: An optional value that identifies the number of significant digits for the returned percentage, three digits if omitted (0.xxx%).

PERCENTRANK_INC.name: PERCENTRANK_INC
PERCENTRANK_INC.description: Returns the rank of a value in a data set as a percentage (0..1, inclusive) of the data set.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The array or range of data with numeric values that defines relative standing.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The value for which the rank will be returned.

params.name: arg3
params.description: An optional value that identifies the number of significant digits for the returned percentage, three digits if omitted (0.xxx%).

PERMUT.name: PERMUT
PERMUT.description: Returns the number of permutations for a given number of objects that can be selected from the total objects.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The total number of objects.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The number of objects in each permutation.

PERMUTATIONA.name: PERMUTATIONA
PERMUTATIONA.description: Returns the number of permutations for a given number of objects (with repetitions) that can be selected from the total objects.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The total number of objects.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The number of objects in each permutation.

PHI.name: PHI
PHI.description: Returns the value of the density function for a standard normal distribution.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The number for which the density of the standard normal distribution will be returned.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The number of events.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The expected numeric value, a positive number.

params.name: arg3
params.description: A logical value (true or false) that determines the function form. If it is true, the function returns the cumulative Poisson probability. If it is false, the function returns the Poisson probability mass function.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The number of events.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The expected numeric value, a positive number.

params.name: arg3
params.description: A logical value (true or false) that determines the function form. If it is true, the function returns the cumulative Poisson probability. If it is false, the function returns the Poisson probability mass function.

QUARTILE.name: QUARTILE
QUARTILE.description: Returns the quartile of a data set.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The array or cell range of numeric values for which the quartile value will be returned.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The quartile value to return: minimum value = 0; 1st quartile = 1; median value = 2; 3rd quartile = 3; maximum value = 4.

QUARTILE_EXC.name: QUARTILE_EXC
QUARTILE_EXC.description: Returns the quartile of a data set, based on percentile values from 0..1, exclusive.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The array or cell range of numeric values for which the quartile value will be returned.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The quartile value to return: 1st quartile = 1; median value = 2; 3rd quartile = 3.

QUARTILE_INC.name: QUARTILE_INC
QUARTILE_INC.description: Returns the quartile of a data set, based on percentile values from 0..1, inclusive.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The array or cell range of numeric values for which the quartile value will be returned.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The quartile value to return: minimum value = 0; 1st quartile = 1; median value = 2; 3rd quartile = 3; maximum value = 4.

RANK.name: RANK
RANK.description: Returns the rank of a number in a list of numbers: its size relative to other values in the list.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The number for which the rank will be returned.

params.name: arg2
params.description: An array of numbers or a reference to a list of numbers. Nonnumeric values are ignored.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The numeric value that specifyes how to order the numbers. If it is 0 or omitted, the rank in the list will be sorted in descending order. Any other numeric value means that the rank in the list will be sorted in ascending order.

RANK_AVG.name: RANK_AVG
RANK_AVG.description: Returns the rank of a number in a list of numbers: its size relative to other values in the list. If more than one value has the same rank, the average rank is returned.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The number for which the rank will be returned.

params.name: arg2
params.description: An array of numbers or a reference to a list of numbers. Nonnumeric values are ignored.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The numeric value that specifyes how to order the numbers. If it is 0 or omitted, the rank in the list will be sorted in descending order. Any other numeric value means that the rank in the list will be sorted in ascending order.

RANK_EQ.name: RANK_EQ
RANK_EQ.description: Returns the rank of a number in a list of numbers: its size relative to other values in the list. If more than one value has the same rank, the top rank of that set of values is returned.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The number for which the rank will be returned.

params.name: arg2
params.description: An array of numbers or a reference to a list of numbers. Nonnumeric values are ignored.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The numeric value that specifyes how to order the numbers. If it is 0 or omitted, the rank in the list will be sorted in descending order. Any other numeric value means that the rank in the list will be sorted in ascending order.

SKEW.name: SKEW
SKEW.description: Returns the skewness of a distribution: a characterization of the degree of asymmetry of a distribution around its mean.

params.name: args
params.description: Up to 255 numeric values for which the skewness of a distribution will be returned. The first argument is required, subsequent arguments are optional.

SKEW_P.name: SKEW_P
SKEW_P.description: Returns the skewness of a distribution based on a population: a characterization of the degree of asymmetry of a distribution around its mean.

params.name: args
params.description: Up to 255 numeric values for which the skewness of a distribution will be returned. The first argument is required, subsequent arguments are optional.

SMALL.name: SMALL
SMALL.description: Returns the k-th smallest value in a data set. For example, the fifth smallest number.

params.name: arg1
params.description: An array or range of numerical data for which the k-th smallest value will be determined.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The position (from the smallest) in the array or range of the value to return.

STANDARDIZE.name: STANDARDIZE
STANDARDIZE.description: Returns a normalised value from a distribution characterised by a mean and standard deviation.

params.name: arg1
params.description: The value to normalize.

params.name: arg2
params.description: The arithmetic mean of the distribution.

params.name: arg3
params.description: The standard deviation of the distribution, a positive number.

STDEV.name: STDEV
STDEV.description: Estimates standard deviation based on a sample (ignores logical values and text in the sample).

params.name: args
params.description: Up to 255 numeric values for which the standard deviation will be calculated. The first argument is required, subsequent arguments are optional.

STDEV_S.name: STDEV_S
STDEV_S.description: Estimates standard deviation based on a sample (ignores logical values and text in the sample).

params.name: args
params.description: Up to 255 numeric values for which the standard deviation will be calculated. The first argument is required, subsequent arguments are optional.

STDEVA.name: STDEVA
STDEVA.description: Estimates standard deviation based on a sample, including logical values and text. Text and the false logical value have the value 0; the true logical value has the value 1.

params.name: args
params.description: Up to 255 values for which the standard deviation will be calculated. The first argument is required, subsequent arguments are optional.

STDEVP.name: STDEVP

DVAR.name: DVAR

params.name: arg2

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is the security's annual coupon rate.

params.name: arg5

params.name: arg6
params.description: Is the number of coupon payments per year.

params.name: arg7
params.description: Is the type of day count basis to use.

params.name: arg8
params.description: Is a logical value: to accrued interest from issue date = TRUE or omitted; to calculate from last coupon payment date = FALSE.

ACCRINTM.name: ACCRINTM
ACCRINTM.description: Returns the accrued interest for a security that pays interest at maturity.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the security's issue date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the security's maturity date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the security's annual coupon rate.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is the security's par value.

params.name: arg5
params.description: Is the type of day count basis to use.

AMORDEGRC.name: AMORDEGRC
AMORDEGRC.description: Returns the prorated linear depreciation of an asset for each accounting period..

AMORLINC.name: AMORLINC
AMORLINC.description: Returns the prorated linear depreciation of an asset for each accounting period..

params.description: Is the date the asset is purchased.

params.name: arg4

params.name: arg5
